@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Help";
}

<h2>Help & System Overview</h2>

<p class="text-muted">
    Welcome to the Accounting System. This page provides an overview of system features and how to use them.
</p>

<hr />

<h5>🔐 Login & Security</h5>
<ul>
    <li>Users must log in using their assigned credentials.</li>
    <li>The system supports three roles: <strong>Administrator</strong>, <strong>Manager</strong>, and <strong>Accountant</strong>.</li>
    <li>Accounts are locked after multiple failed login attempts.</li>
    <li>Passwords must meet security requirements and expire periodically.</li>
    <li>The “Forgot Password” feature allows users to reset their password using security verification.</li>
</ul>

<h5>👤 User Access Requests</h5>
<ul>
    <li>New users must request access through the <strong>Create New User</strong> page.</li>
    <li>Administrators review and approve or reject requests.</li>
    <li>Approved users receive login credentials.</li>
</ul>

<h5>🗂 Chart of Accounts</h5>
<ul>
    <li>Administrators can create, edit, and deactivate accounts.</li>
    <li>Accounts include categories, subcategories, and balances.</li>
    <li>Duplicate account names or numbers are not allowed.</li>
    <li>Clicking an account opens its ledger view.</li>
    <li>Search and filter tools help locate accounts quickly.</li>
</ul>

<h5>📘 Journal & Ledger</h5>
<ul>
    <li>Users can create journal entries with debit and credit lines.</li>
    <li>Managers approve or reject journal entries.</li>
    <li>Approved entries can be posted to the ledger.</li>
    <li>The ledger displays account balances and transaction history.</li>
</ul>

<h5>📊 Reports & Future Features</h5>
<ul>
    <li>Financial statements (Income Statement, Balance Sheet, etc.) will be available in later sprints.</li>
    <li>Ratio analysis and dashboards will be added in future releases.</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h5>🧭 Navigation Tips</h5>
<ul>
    <li>Use the top navigation bar to access system features.</li>
    <li>Administrator tools are available under the <strong>Admin</strong> menu.</li>
    <li>Click your name in the top right to manage your account or log out.</li>
</ul>

<h5>📩 Support</h5>
<p>
    If you experience issues, please contact your system administrator or refer to the system documentation.
</p>